obo:ECO_0000314  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_2552  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: From Results section:\n\n\"Consistent with the results from yeast two-hybrid interaction assay, we found that\nNR2C, but not NR2A and NR2B, coimmunoprecipitated with 14-3-33ε (Figure 1D), demonstrating that NR2C is a specific binding partner for 14-3-33ε in vivo.\"\n\n\"Surface expression of NR2C WT was dramatically decreased upon cotransfection with 14-3-33ε dn (Figure 4), indicating that the interaction between NR2C and 14-3-3ε is required for NR2C trafficking. In addition, surface expression of NR2C S1096A was much less than that of NR2C WT when 14-3-33ε was coexpressed\nand was further reduced upon coexpression with 14-3-33ε dn (Figure 4), suggesting that S1096 is not the sole molecular determinant in 14-3-33-regulated NR2C trafficking.\". Experimental description: From fig 1d:\nAdult rat cerebella were solubilized, and 14-3-33ε was immunoprecipitated from lysates with anti-14-3-33 antibodies or IgG antibodies as a control.\n\nFrom fig 4:\nCerebellar granule cells were cotransfected with NR2C containing an extracellular GFP protein tag (GFP-NR2C) or GFP-NR2C S1096A and Myc-14-3-33 WT or Myc-14-3-33ε dn." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6893-6177" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5265-6306" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-16" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2552" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

